• Total Revenue = 3025437.82

Step 2: Determine the total assets from the balance sheet at the beginning and at the end.  
• Beginning Total Assets = 13000000.00  
• Ending Total Assets = 14930535.06

Step 3: Calculate the Average Total Assets.  
• Average Total Assets = (13000000.00 + 14930535.06) / 2  
• Average Total Assets = 27930535.06 / 2  
• Average Total Assets ≈ 13965267.53

Step 4: Calculate the Total Asset Turnover Ratio by dividing Total Revenue by Average Total Assets.  
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio = 3025437.82 / 13965267.53  
• Total Asset Turnover Ratio ≈ 0.2166, which rounds to 0.22
